"searchKeywords":["and","all","the","kings","lam","persians"]},{"verseId":"brenton_jeremiah_32_26","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":46,"bookName":"Jeremiah","bookAbbrev":"jeremiah","chapter":32,"verse":26,"text":"and all the kings from the north, the far and the near, each one with his brother, and all the kingdoms which are on the face of the earth.","searchKeywords":["and","all","the","kings","from","north","far","near","each","one","with","his","brother","kingdoms","which","are","face","earth"]},{"verseId":"brenton_jeremiah_32_27","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":46,"bookName":"Jeremiah","bookAbbrev":"jeremiah","chapter":32,"verse":27,"text":"And thou shalt say to them, Thus said the Lord Almighty; Drink ye, be ye drunken; and ye shall vomit, and shall fall, and shall in nowise rise, because of the sword which I send among you.","searchKeywords":["and","thou","shalt","say","them","thus","said","the","lord","almighty","drink","drunken","shall","vomit","fall","nowise","rise","because","sword","which","send","among","you"]},{"verseId":"brenton_jeremiah_32_28","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":46,"bookName":"Jeremiah","bookAbbrev":"jeremiah","chapter":32,"verse":28,"text":"And it shall come to pass, when they refuse to take the cup out of thine hand, to drink it, that thou shalt say, Thus said the Lord; Ye shall surely drink.","searchKeywords":["and","shall","come","pass","when","they","refuse","take","the","cup","out","thine","hand","drink","that","thou","shalt","say","thus","said","lord","surely"]},{"verseId":"brenton_jeremiah_32_29","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":46,"bookName":"Jeremiah","bookAbbrev":"jeremiah","chapter":32,"verse":29,"text":"For I am beginning to afflict the city whereon my name is called, and ye shall by no means be held guiltless: for I am calling a sword upon all that dwell upon the earth.","searchKeywords":["for","beginning","afflict","the","city","whereon","name","called","and","shall","means","held","guiltless","calling","sword","upon","all","that","dwell","earth"]},{"verseId":"brenton_jeremiah_32_30","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":46,"bookName":"Jeremiah","bookAbbrev":"jeremiah","chapter":32,"verse":30,"text":"And thou shalt prophesy against them these words, and shalt say, The Lord shall speak from on high, from his sanctuary he will utter his voice; he will pronounce a declaration on his place; and these shall answer like men gathering grapes: and destruction is coming on them that dwell on the earth,","searchKeywords":["and","thou","shalt","prophesy","against","them","these","words","say","the","lord","shall","speak","from","high","his","sanctuary","will","utter","voice","pronounce","declaration","place","answer","like","men","gathering","grapes","destruction","coming","that","dwell","earth"]},{"verseId":"brenton_jeremiah_32_31","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":46,"bookName":"Jeremiah","bookAbbrev":"jeremiah","chapter":32,"verse":31,"text":"upon part of the earth; for the Lord a controversy with the nations, he is pleading with all flesh, and the ungodly are given to the sword, saith the Lord.","searchKeywords":["upon","part","the","earth","for","lord","controversy","with","nations","pleading","all","flesh","and","ungodly","are","given","sword","saith"]},{"verseId":"brenton_jeremiah_32_32","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":46,"bookName":"Jeremiah","bookAbbrev":"jeremiah","chapter":32,"verse":32,"text":"Thus said the Lord; Behold, evils are proceeding from nation to nation, and a great whirlwind goes forth from the end of the earth.","searchKeywords":["thus","said","the","lord","behold","evils","are","proceeding","from","nation","and","great","whirlwind","goes","forth","end","earth"]},{"verseId":"brenton_jeremiah_32_33","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":46,"bookName":"Jeremiah","bookAbbrev":"jeremiah","chapter":32,"verse":33,"text":"And the slain of the Lord shall be in the day of the Lord from end of the earth even to the end of the earth: they shall not be buried; they shall be as dung on the face of the earth.","searchKeywords":["and","the","slain","lord","shall","day","from","end","earth","even","they","not","buried","dung","face"]},{"verseId":"brenton_jeremiah_32_34","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":46,"bookName":"Jeremiah","bookAbbrev":"jeremiah","chapter":32,"verse":34,"text":"Howl, ye shepherds, and cry; and lament, ye rams of the flock: for your days have been completed for slaughter, and ye shall fall as the choice rams.","searchKeywords":["howl","shepherds","and","cry","lament","rams","the","flock","for","your","days","have","been","completed","slaughter","shall","fall","choice"]},{"verseId":"brenton_jeremiah_32_35","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":46,"bookName":"Jeremiah","bookAbbrev":"jeremiah","chapter":32,"verse":35,"text":"And flight shall perish from the shepherds, and safety from the rams of the flock.","searchKeywords":["and","flight","shall","perish","from","the","shepherds","safety","rams","flock"]},{"verseId":"brenton_jeremiah_32_36","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":46,"bookName":"Jeremiah","bookAbbrev":"jeremiah","chapter":32,"verse":36,"text":"A voice of the crying of the shepherds, and a moaning of the sheep and the rams: for the Lord has destroyed their pastures.","searchKeywords":["voice","the","crying","shepherds","and","moaning","sheep","rams","for","lord","has","destroyed","their","pastures"]},{"verseId":"brenton_jeremiah_32_37","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":46,"bookName":"Jeremiah","bookAbbrev":"jeremiah","chapter":32,"verse":37,"text":"And the peaceable abodes that remain shall be destroyed before the fierceness of my anger.","searchKeywords":["and","the","peaceable","abodes","that","remain","shall","destroyed","before","fierceness","anger"]},{"verseId":"brenton_jeremiah_32_38","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":46,"bookName":"Jeremiah","bookAbbrev":"jeremiah","chapter":32,"verse":38,"text":"He has forsaken his lair, as a lion: for their land is become desolate before the great sword.","searchKeywords":["has","forsaken","his","lair","lion","for","their","land","become","desolate","before","the","great","sword"]}]